							</div>

							<!-- Explanation callout -->
							<div class="bg-slate-900/50 border border-white/[0.04] p-4 rounded-xl mt-3 flex flex-col gap-3">
								<div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-emerald-400 font-semibold text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">
									<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4.5 h-4.5">
										<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.879 7.519c1.171-1.025 3.071-1.025 4.242 0 1.172 1.025 1.172 2.687 0 3.712-.203.179-.43.326-.67.442-.745.361-1.45.999-1.45 1.827v.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0zm-9 5.25h.008v.008H12v-.008z" />
									</svg>
									<span>Why are these Protocols & Ports used?</span>
								</div>
								<div class="flex flex-col gap-2.5 text-xs text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
									<p>💡 <strong class="text-gray-300">Why SMTP Protocol?</strong> Simple Mail Transfer Protocol (SMTP) is the only universal language used by mail servers (Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo) to exchange emails. Unlike fetching protocols like IMAP/POP3, SMTP is designed specifically for mail routing and push delivery.</p>
									<p>🔌 <strong class="text-gray-300">Why Port 25 for Live & 2525 for Local?</strong> 
										<br>• <strong class="text-gray-300">Port 25:</strong> The worldwide standard port for inter-server email transmission. External mail systems strictly target port 25 to send emails to your domain. 
										<br>• <strong class="text-gray-300">Port 2525:</strong> Used locally because ports under 1024 are restricted to administrator/root accounts on macOS/Linux. Using 2525 avoids requiring root permissions during development.
									</p>
									<p>🌐 <strong class="text-gray-300">Why HTTP Protocol & Port 8081?</strong> The frontend dashboard fetches email JSON data via the HTTP protocol. Running HTTP on port <code class="bg-black/30 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-emerald-400 font-mono">8081</code> separates web API requests from incoming mail traffic, preventing database lockups or latency issues.</p>
									<p>📂 <strong class="text-gray-300">Where are these configured in the code?</strong>
										<br>• The ports are defined in <a href="file:///Users/mac/Documents/react/temp-email/backend/receive-mail/receive-mail.js#L8-L9" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">receive-mail/receive-mail.js (lines 8-9)</a>.
										<br>• The API URL is configured in the script tag in <a href="file:///Users/mac/Documents/react/temp-email/src/pages/live.astro#L315-L316" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">src/pages/live.astro (lines 315-316)</a>.
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<!-- Content 2: VPS & Domain Setup -->
						<div id="vps-setup-help" class="help-tab-pane hidden flex flex-col gap-4">
							<h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base flex items-center gap-2">
								<span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-emerald-500 rounded"></span>
								DigitalOcean VPS & Domain Configuration
							</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-400 text-xs">Follow this step-by-step guide to run TempEmail on a DigitalOcean droplet and connect your domain (Hostinger, Namecheap, etc.):</p>
							
							<ol class="list-decimal pl-5 flex flex-col gap-4 text-gray-400 text-xs">
								<li>
									<strong class="text-white text-sm block mb-1">Create a Droplet (VPS)</strong>
									Deploy a basic Ubuntu VPS on DigitalOcean. Since the Node.js SMTP service is extremely lightweight, the entry-level $4/month tier (512MB RAM / 1 vCPU) is more than sufficient.
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong class="text-white text-sm block mb-1">Configure VPS Firewall (UFW)</strong>
									Connect to your VPS via SSH and open incoming network ports. You must enable SMTP port 25 and HTTP ports:
									<pre class="bg-black/50 p-2.5 rounded font-mono text-[10px] text-emerald-300 mt-1.5 select-all">{"sudo ufw allow 25/tcp\nsudo ufw allow 80/tcp\nsudo ufw allow 8081/tcp\nsudo ufw enable"}</pre>
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong class="text-white text-sm block mb-1">Setup Persistent Process with PM2</strong>
									Deploy your code, install dependencies, and run the server in the background using PM2 so it stays active when you log off:
									<pre class="bg-black/50 p-2.5 rounded font-mono text-[10px] text-emerald-300 mt-1.5 select-all">{"sudo npm install -g pm2\npm2 start backend/receive-mail/receive-mail.js --name \"temp-email\"\npm2 save && pm2 startup"}</pre>
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong class="text-white text-sm block mb-1">Connect Your Domain (DNS Settings)</strong>
									Log into your domain provider (Hostinger, Namecheap, GoDaddy, etc.) and add the following two DNS records:
									<div class="bg-slate-900/40 border border-white/[0.04] p-3 rounded-lg mt-2 flex flex-col gap-2">
										<p><strong>1. A Record (Mail Subdomain):</strong></p>
										<ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-400">
											<li><strong>Type:</strong> <code class="text-white font-mono">A</code></li>
											<li><strong>Name / Host:</strong> <code class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">mail</code></li>
											<li><strong>Points to:</strong> <code class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">YOUR_VPS_IP</code></li>
										</ul>
										<p class="border-t border-white/[0.04] pt-2"><strong>2. MX Record (Mail Server Route):</strong></p>
										<ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-400">
											<li><strong>Type:</strong> <code class="text-white font-mono">MX</code></li>
											<li><strong>Name / Host:</strong> <code class="text-white font-mono">@</code> (or blank)</li>
											<li><strong>Points to:</strong> <code class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">mail.yourdomain.com</code></li>
											<li><strong>Priority:</strong> <code class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">10</code></li>
										</ul>
									</div>
									<em class="text-amber-400/80 block mt-1 text-[11px]">*Important: You MUST delete any default MX records provided by Hostinger/Namecheap. If multiple MX records coexist, public email delivery will fail or route incorrectly.</em>
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong class="text-white text-sm block mb-1">Support Multiple Domains</strong>
									This server automatically catches incoming traffic for all configured domains. To receive emails on other domains, simply point their MX records to your server subdomain (<code class="text-white font-mono">mail.otherdomain.com</code> -> VPS IP).
								</li>
								<li>
									<strong class="text-white text-sm block mb-1">Send a Real Test Email</strong>
									Once DNS records propagate (typically takes 5 to 15 minutes), send an email from your personal Gmail or Outlook account to <code class="text-white font-semibold">anything@yourdomain.com</code>. It will appear on this console interface in real-time.
								</li>
							</ol>

							<!-- Explanation callout -->
							<div class="bg-slate-900/50 border border-white/[0.04] p-4 rounded-xl mt-3 flex flex-col gap-3">
								<div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-emerald-400 font-semibold text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">
									<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4.5 h-4.5">
										<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.879 7.519c1.171-1.025 3.071-1.025 4.242 0 1.172 1.025 1.172 2.687 0 3.712-.203.179-.43.326-.67.442-.745.361-1.45.999-1.45 1.827v.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0zm-9 5.25h.008v.008H12v-.008z" />
									</svg>
									<span>Why do we use PM2, MX & A Records, and sudo?</span>
								</div>
								<div class="flex flex-col gap-2.5 text-xs text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
									<p>🤖 <strong class="text-gray-300">Why PM2 Process Manager?</strong> PM2 runs your Node.js server in the background as a persistent system daemon. This ensures the email service stays active when your terminal is closed, automatically restarts if it crashes, and boots up on system startup.</p>
									<p>🔑 <strong class="text-gray-300">Why "sudo" is required?</strong> On Linux/Unix servers, binding to privileged ports below 1024 (like port 25 for SMTP or port 80 for HTTP) requires administrator/root permissions. The <code class="bg-black/30 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-emerald-400 font-mono">sudo</code> prefix grants these elevated permissions.</p>
									<p>📋 <strong class="text-gray-300">Why MX & A Records?</strong> DNS records instruct external servers where to route requests:
										<br>• <strong class="text-gray-300">A Record:</strong> Maps the hostname <code class="text-white">mail.yourdomain.com</code> to your VPS IP address.
										<br>• <strong class="text-gray-300">MX Record:</strong> Designates the mail server host for your domain, forwarding all email traffic for <code class="text-white">@yourdomain.com</code> directly to your VPS hostname.
									</p>
									<p>📂 <strong class="text-gray-300">Where are these configured in the code?</strong>
										<br>• In production, ports are overridden using env variables (<code class="text-white">SMTP_PORT=25</code> and <code class="text-white">HTTP_PORT=80</code>) defined inside the PM2 startup configuration or shell.
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

		<!-- Client side Script for Real-Time Updating -->
		<script is:inline>
			const API_BASE = "http://localhost:8081";
			const API_URL = window.location.port === "4321" ? API_BASE : `${window.location.protocol}//${window.location.host}`;

			let emailsData = [];
			let selectedEmailId = null;
			let knownEmailIds = null;

			function playBellSound() {
				const audio = new Audio("/bell.wav");
				audio.play().catch(err => {
					console.warn("Audio playback failed (interaction required):", err);
				});
			}

			// Tab Switching Logic
			const tabButtons = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn');
			const tabPanes = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-pane');

			tabButtons.forEach(btn => {
				btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
					tabButtons.forEach(b => {
						b.classList.remove('text-white', 'bg-white/[0.05]', 'active-tab');
						b.classList.add('text-gray-400');
					});
					tabPanes.forEach(p => p.classList.add('hidden'));

					btn.classList.add('text-white', 'bg-white/[0.05]', 'active-tab');
					btn.classList.remove('text-gray-400');
					
					const targetPane = document.getElementById(btn.getAttribute('data-tab'));
					if (targetPane) targetPane.classList.remove('hidden');
				});
			});

			const activeTabBtn = document.querySelector('.tab-btn.active-tab');
			if (activeTabBtn) {
				activeTabBtn.classList.add('text-white', 'bg-white/[0.05]');
				activeTabBtn.classList.remove('text-gray-400');
			}

			// Visibility of Delete Selected Button
			function updateDeleteSelectedBtnVisibility() {
				const checked = document.querySelectorAll('.email-checkbox:checked');
				const btn = document.getElementById('deleteSelectedBtn');
				if (btn) {
					if (checked.length > 0) {
						btn.classList.remove('hidden');
					} else {
						btn.classList.add('hidden');
					}
				}
			}

			// Fetch Emails from API
			async function fetchEmails() {
				try {
					const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/api/emails/live`);
					if (!res.ok) throw new Error("API Connection Failed");
					const data = await res.json();
					
					// Play sound if a new email is received
					if (knownEmailIds !== null) {
						let hasNewEmail = false;
						data.forEach(email => {
							if (!knownEmailIds.has(email.id)) {
								hasNewEmail = true;
							}
						});
						if (hasNewEmail) {
							playBellSound();
						}
					}
					knownEmailIds = new Set(data.map(email => email.id));

					emailsData = data;
					document.getElementById('emailCount').textContent = data.length;
					renderEmailList(data);
					
					if (selectedEmailId) {
						const currentSelected = data.find(e => e.id === selectedEmailId);
						if (currentSelected) {
							renderEmailReader(currentSelected);
							document.getElementById('rawJsonCode').textContent = JSON.stringify(currentSelected, null, 2);
						}
					}
				} catch (err) {
					console.error("Error fetching emails:", err);
				}
			}

			// Fetch logs
			async function fetchLogs() {
				try {
					// 1. Fetch Receiving Logs
					const resRec = await fetch(`${API_URL}/api/logs/live/receiving`);
					if (resRec.ok) {
						const logsRec = await resRec.json();
						const logsCode = document.getElementById('systemLogsCode');
						if (logsCode) {
							logsCode.textContent = logsRec.join('\n');
						}
					}
					
					// 2. Fetch Sending Logs
					const resSend = await fetch(`${API_URL}/api/logs/live/sending`);
					if (resSend.ok) {
						const logsSend = await resSend.json();
						const sendingCode = document.getElementById('sendingLogsCode');
						if (sendingCode) {
							sendingCode.textContent = logsSend.join('\n');
						}
					}
				} catch (err) {
					console.error("Error fetching logs:", err);
				}
			}

			// Render Sidebar List
			function renderEmailList(emails) {
				const container = document.getElementById('emailListContainer');
				if (!container) return;

				if (emails.length === 0) {
					container.innerHTML = `
						<div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-16 px-8 text-gray-500 gap-2">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-10 h-10 text-gray-600">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 13.5h3.86a2.25 2.25 0 012.008 1.24l.885 1.77a2.25 2.25 0 002.007 1.24h1.98a2.25 2.25 0 002.007-1.24l.885-1.77a2.25 2.25 0 012.007-1.24h3.86m-18 0h18m-18 0V9A2.25 2.25 0 014.5 6.75h15A2.25 2.25 0 0121.75 9v4.5m-18 0V18a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0021 18v-4.5m-15 0V9a1.5 1.5 0 00-1.5-1.5H5.25A1.5 1.5 0 003.75 9v4.5m16.5 0V9a1.5 1.5 0 00-1.5-1.5h-1.5A1.5 1.5 0 0015.75 9v4.5" />
							</svg>
							<p class="text-sm">Waiting for live emails...</p>
						</div>
					`;
					return;
				}

				const previouslyCheckedFilenames = new Set(
					Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.email-checkbox:checked')).map(cb => cb.getAttribute('data-filename'))
				);

				const readEmails = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('liveReadEmails') || '[]');
				const readEmailSet = new Set(readEmails);

				container.innerHTML = emails.map(email => {
					const dateStr = new Date(email.date).toLocaleTimeString([], { hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit' });
					const isSelected = email.id === selectedEmailId ? 'bg-emerald-500/5 border-l-2 border-emerald-400' : 'border-l-2 border-transparent';
					
					const hasAttachment = email.attachments && email.attachments.length > 0;
					const attachmentSvg = hasAttachment ? `
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-gray-500 inline-block align-middle ml-1">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M18.375 12.739l-7.693 7.693a4.5 4.5 0 01-6.364-6.364l10.94-10.94A3 3 0 1119.5 7.372L8.552 18.32m.009-.01l-.01.01m5.699-9.941l-7.81 7.81a1.5 1.5 0 002.112 2.13" />
						</svg>
					` : '';

					const isChecked = previouslyCheckedFilenames.has(email.fileName) ? 'checked' : '';

					const isRead = readEmailSet.has(email.id);
					const readBadge = isRead ? `
						<span class="text-[9px] font-bold px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-white/[0.04] text-gray-500 border border-white/[0.05] uppercase tracking-wider">Read</span>
					` : `
						<span class="text-[9px] font-bold px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/20 uppercase tracking-wider animate-pulse">New</span>
					`;
					
					const fontClass = isRead ? 'font-normal text-gray-400' : 'font-bold text-white';
					const subjectFontClass = isRead ? 'font-medium text-gray-300' : 'font-semibold text-white';

					return `
						<div class="p-4 border-b border-white/[0.04] cursor-pointer transition-colors hover:bg-white/[0.01] flex gap-3 items-start ${isSelected}" data-id="${email.id}">
							<input type="checkbox" class="email-checkbox mt-0.5 cursor-pointer" data-filename="${email.fileName}" ${isChecked}>
							<div class="flex-grow flex flex-col gap-1.5 overflow-hidden">
								<div class="flex justify-between items-center">
									<span class="text-xs ${fontClass} overflow-hidden text-ellipsis whitespace-nowrap max-w-[180px]">${escapeHTML(email.from)}</span>
									<div class="flex items-center gap-2">
										${readBadge}
										<span class="text-[10px] text-gray-500 font-mono">${dateStr}</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="text-xs overflow-hidden text-ellipsis whitespace-nowrap flex items-center justify-between ${subjectFontClass}">
									<span>${escapeHTML(email.subject)}</span>
									${attachmentSvg}
								</div>
								<div class="text-[11px] text-gray-400 line-clamp-2 leading-relaxed">${escapeHTML(email.text.slice(0, 50))}${email.text.length > 50 ? '...' : ''}</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					`;
				}).join('');

				document.querySelectorAll('[data-id]').forEach(item => {
					item.addEventListener('click', () => {
						const emailId = item.getAttribute('data-id');
						selectEmail(emailId);
					});

					const checkbox = item.querySelector('.email-checkbox');
					if (checkbox) {
						checkbox.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
							e.stopPropagation();
							updateDeleteSelectedBtnVisibility();
						});
					}
				});
				updateDeleteSelectedBtnVisibility();
			}

			function selectEmail(id) {
				selectedEmailId = id;
				const email = emailsData.find(e => e.id === id);
				if (email) {
					// Mark as read in localStorage
					let readEmails = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('liveReadEmails') || '[]');
					if (!readEmails.includes(id)) {
						readEmails.push(id);
						localStorage.setItem('liveReadEmails', JSON.stringify(readEmails));
					}

					renderEmailReader(email);
					document.getElementById('rawJsonCode').textContent = JSON.stringify(email, null, 2);
					fetchEmails();
				}
			}

			// Render Email Detail
			function renderEmailReader(email) {
				const container = document.getElementById('emailReaderContainer');
				if (!container) return;

				const dateStr = new Date(email.date).toLocaleString();
				const hasAttachments = email.attachments && email.attachments.length > 0;

				container.innerHTML = `
					<div class="p-6 border-b border-white/[0.06] flex flex-col gap-3">
						<div class="flex justify-between items-start gap-4">
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">${escapeHTML(email.subject)}</h2>
							<button class="bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/25 hover:bg-red-500/25 text-red-400 px-3.5 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-xs font-semibold cursor-pointer transition-colors" id="deleteMailBtn" data-filename="${email.fileName}">Delete Email</button>
						</div>
						<div class="flex flex-col gap-1 text-xs text-gray-300">
							<div><strong>From:</strong> ${escapeHTML(email.from)}</div>
							<div><strong>To:</strong> ${escapeHTML(email.to)}</div>
							<div class="flex gap-4 text-gray-500 text-[10px] mt-1.5 font-mono">
								<span>Time: ${dateStr}</span>
								<span>Sender IP: ${email.senderIp}</span>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="flex-grow flex flex-col p-5 gap-3">
						<div class="flex gap-2 border-b border-white/[0.05] pb-2">
							<button class="bg-white/[0.05] text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs font-medium cursor-pointer" id="btnShowHtml">Rich Text (HTML)</button>
							<button class="text-gray-400 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs font-medium cursor-pointer hover:text-white" id="btnShowText">Plain Text</button>
						</div>
						<div class="flex-grow bg-black/30 rounded-xl border border-white/[0.05] overflow-hidden min-h-[280px] flex">
							<div id="htmlContent" class="w-full flex-grow flex">
								${email.html ? `<iframe srcdoc="${escapeIframe(email.html)}" class="w-full h-full border-none bg-white" sandbox="allow-same-origin" title="Email content"></iframe>` : `<pre class="p-5 whitespace-pre-wrap break-all font-mono text-xs text-gray-200 overflow-y-auto w-full">${escapeHTML(email.text)}</pre>`}
							</div>
							<div id="textContent" class="w-full flex-grow flex hidden">
								<pre class="p-5 whitespace-pre-wrap break-all font-mono text-xs text-gray-200 overflow-y-auto w-full">${escapeHTML(email.text)}</pre>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					${hasAttachments ? `
						<div class="p-5 bg-white/[0.01] border-t border-white/[0.06] flex flex-col gap-3">
							<h4 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-400 flex items-center gap-1.5">
								<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4.5 h-4.5">
									<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M18.375 12.739l-7.693 7.693a4.5 4.5 0 01-6.364-6.364l10.94-10.94A3 3 0 1119.5 7.372L8.552 18.32m.009-.01l-.01.01m5.699-9.941l-7.81 7.81a1.5 1.5 0 002.112 2.13" />
								</svg>
								<span>Attachments (${email.attachments.length})</span>
							</h4>
							<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
								${email.attachments.map(att => {
									const isImage = att.contentType && att.contentType.startsWith('image/');
									return `
									<a href="${att.url}" target="_blank" class="bg-slate-900 border border-white/[0.06] rounded-lg p-3 flex items-center gap-3 max-w-[280px] hover:bg-slate-800 transition-colors cursor-pointer group">
										${isImage 
											? `<img src="${att.url}" class="w-10 h-10 object-cover rounded bg-white/5" alt="thumbnail" />` 
											: `<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-400"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 14.25v-2.625a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375h-1.5A1.125 1.125 0 0113.5 7.125v-1.5a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375H8.25M9 16.5v.75m3-3v3m3-6v6m-10.125-3H18.75m-16.5 4.5h16.5" /></svg>`
										}
										<div class="flex flex-col overflow-hidden">
											<span class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-200 overflow-hidden text-ellipsis whitespace-nowrap group-hover:text-blue-400">${escapeHTML(att.filename)}</span>
											<span class="text-[10px] text-gray-500 font-mono mt-0.5">${formatBytes(att.size)} &bull; Download</span>
										</div>
									</a>
								`}).join('')}
							</div>
						</div>
					` : ''}
				`;

				const btnShowHtml = document.getElementById('btnShowHtml');
				const btnShowText = document.getElementById('btnShowText');
				const htmlContent = document.getElementById('htmlContent');
				const textContent = document.getElementById('textContent');

				if (btnShowHtml && btnShowText && htmlContent && textContent) {
					btnShowHtml.addEventListener('click', () => {
						btnShowHtml.classList.add('bg-white/[0.05]', 'text-white');
						btnShowHtml.classList.remove('text-gray-400');
						btnShowText.classList.remove('bg-white/[0.05]', 'text-white');
						btnShowText.classList.add('text-gray-400');
						htmlContent.classList.remove('hidden');
						textContent.classList.add('hidden');
					});

					btnShowText.addEventListener('click', () => {
						btnShowText.classList.add('bg-white/[0.05]', 'text-white');
						btnShowText.classList.remove('text-gray-400');
						btnShowHtml.classList.remove('bg-white/[0.05]', 'text-white');
						btnShowHtml.classList.add('text-gray-400');
						textContent.classList.remove('hidden');
						htmlContent.classList.add('hidden');
					});
				}

				const deleteMailBtn = document.getElementById('deleteMailBtn');
				if (deleteMailBtn) {
					deleteMailBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
						const filename = deleteMailBtn.getAttribute('data-filename');
						try {
							const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/api/emails/delete/live/${filename}`, { method: 'POST' });
							if (res.ok) {
								selectedEmailId = null;
								fetchEmails();
								container.innerHTML = `
									<div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center flex-grow text-gray-500 gap-3 p-16 text-center">
										<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1" stroke="currentColor" class="w-16 h-16 text-gray-600">
											<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
										</svg>
										<h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-400">Email Deleted</h3>
										<p class="text-sm max-w-xs">Select another email from the sidebar.</p>
									</div>
								`;
								document.getElementById('rawJsonCode').textContent = "// Email deleted";
							}
						} catch (err) {
							console.error(err);
						}
					});
				}
			}

			// Select All / Unselect All Logic
			const selectAllCheckbox = document.getElementById('selectAllCheckbox');
			if (selectAllCheckbox) {
				selectAllCheckbox.addEventListener('change', () => {
					const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('.email-checkbox');
					checkboxes.forEach(cb => cb.checked = selectAllCheckbox.checked);
					updateDeleteSelectedBtnVisibility();
				});
			}

			// Send Email Form Logic
			const sendEmailForm = document.getElementById('sendEmailForm');
			if (sendEmailForm) {
				sendEmailForm.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
					e.preventDefault();
					const btn = document.getElementById('submitSendBtn');
					const alertBox = document.getElementById('sendAlert');
					
					const from = document.getElementById('sendFrom').value;
					const to = document.getElementById('sendTo').value;
					const subject = document.getElementById('sendSubject').value;
					const message = document.getElementById('sendMessage').value;
					const fileInput = document.getElementById('sendAttachments');

					if (!to) {
						alertBox.textContent = 'Recipient "To" address is required';
						alertBox.classList.remove('hidden');
						return;
					}

					// Process attachments
					let attachments = [];
					if (fileInput.files.length > 0) {
						const files = Array.from(fileInput.files);
						const filePromises = files.map(file => {
							return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
								const reader = new FileReader();
								reader.onload = (e) => {
									const base64 = e.target.result.split(',')[1];
									resolve({
										filename: file.name,
										content: base64
									});
								};
								reader.onerror = reject;
								reader.readAsDataURL(file);
							});
						});
						
						btn.innerHTML = `<span class="animate-spin inline-block w-4 h-4 border-2 border-white/30 border-t-white rounded-full"></span> Processing Files...`;
						attachments = await Promise.all(filePromises);
					}

					btn.innerHTML = `<span class="animate-spin inline-block w-4 h-4 border-2 border-white/30 border-t-white rounded-full"></span> Sending...`;
					btn.classList.add('opacity-75', 'cursor-not-allowed');
					alertBox.classList.add('hidden');

					try {
						const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/api/send-email/live`, {
							method: 'POST',
							headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
							body: JSON.stringify({
								from,
								to,
								subject,
								text: message,
								html: message.replace(/\n/g, '<br>'),
								attachments
							})
						});

						const data = await res.json();
						
						if (data.success) {
							alertBox.className = 'rounded-lg px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold mt-2 bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/20';
							alertBox.textContent = '✅ Email sent successfully!';
							alertBox.classList.remove('hidden');
							document.getElementById('sendSubject').value = '';
							document.getElementById('sendMessage').value = '';
						} else {
							throw new Error(data.error || 'Failed to send email');
						}
					} catch (err) {
						alertBox.className = 'rounded-lg px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold mt-2 bg-red-500/10 text-red-400 border border-red-500/20';
						alertBox.textContent = '❌ Error: ' + err.message;
						alertBox.classList.remove('hidden');
					} finally {
						btn.disabled = false;
						btn.innerHTML = `
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-5 h-5">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 12L3.269 3.126A59.768 59.768 0 0121.485 12 59.77 59.77 0 013.27 20.876L5.999 12zm0 0h7.5" />
							</svg>
							<span>Send Email</span>
						`;
						btn.classList.remove('opacity-75', 'cursor-not-allowed');
					}
				});
			}

			// Delete Selected Button Logic (WITHOUT confirmation)
			const deleteSelectedBtn = document.getElementById('deleteSelectedBtn');
			if (deleteSelectedBtn) {
				deleteSelectedBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
					const checked = document.querySelectorAll('.email-checkbox:checked');
					const filenames = Array.from(checked).map(cb => cb.getAttribute('data-filename'));
					if (filenames.length === 0) return;

					deleteSelectedBtn.disabled = true;

					try {
						await Promise.all(filenames.map(filename =>
							fetch(`${API_URL}/api/emails/delete/live/${filename}`, { method: 'POST' })
						));

						if (selectAllCheckbox) selectAllCheckbox.checked = false;
						selectedEmailId = null;

						const reader = document.getElementById('emailReaderContainer');
						if (reader) {
							reader.innerHTML = `
								<div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center flex-grow text-gray-500 gap-3 p-16 text-center">
									<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1" stroke="currentColor" class="w-16 h-16 text-gray-600">
										<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
									</svg>
									<h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-400">Emails Deleted</h3>
									<p class="text-sm max-w-xs">Selected messages deleted successfully.</p>
								</div>
							`;
						}
						document.getElementById('rawJsonCode').textContent = "// Emails deleted";
						fetchEmails();
					} catch (err) {
						console.error("Error deleting selected:", err);
					} finally {
						deleteSelectedBtn.disabled = false;
					}
				});
			}

			// Refresh button
			const refreshBtn = document.getElementById('refreshBtn');
			if (refreshBtn) {
				refreshBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
					fetchEmails();
					fetchLogs();
				});
			}

			function escapeHTML(str) {
				if (!str) return "";
				return str.replace(/&/g, "&amp;").replace(/</g, "&lt;").replace(/>/g, "&gt;").replace(/"/g, "&quot;").replace(/'/g, "&#039;");
			}

			function escapeIframe(html) {
				if (!html) return "";
				return html.replace(/"/g, "&quot;");
			}

			function formatBytes(bytes) {
				if (bytes === 0) return '0 Bytes';
				const k = 1024;
				const sizes = ['Bytes', 'KB', 'MB'];
				const i = Math.floor(Math.log(bytes) / Math.log(k));
				return parseFloat((bytes / Math.pow(k, i)).toFixed(2)) + ' ' + sizes[i];
			}

			// Copy JSON
			const copyJsonBtn = document.getElementById('copyJsonBtn');
			if (copyJsonBtn) {
				copyJsonBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
					const codeText = document.getElementById('rawJsonCode').textContent;
					navigator.clipboard.writeText(codeText);
					copyJsonBtn.textContent = "Copied!";
					setTimeout(() => copyJsonBtn.textContent = "Copy JSON", 2000);
				});
			}

			// Copy Logs
			const copyLogsBtn = document.getElementById('copyLogsBtn');
			if (copyLogsBtn) {
				copyLogsBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
					const codeText = document.getElementById('systemLogsCode').textContent;
					navigator.clipboard.writeText(codeText);
					copyLogsBtn.textContent = "Copied!";
					setTimeout(() => copyLogsBtn.textContent = "Copy Logs", 2000);
				});
			}

			// Help Modal Dialog Logic
			const helpBtn = document.getElementById('helpBtn');
			const helpModal = document.getElementById('helpModal');
			const closeHelpModalBtn = document.getElementById('closeHelpModalBtn');

			if (helpBtn && helpModal && closeHelpModalBtn) {
				helpBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
					helpModal.classList.remove('opacity-0', 'pointer-events-none');
				});
				closeHelpModalBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
					helpModal.classList.add('opacity-0', 'pointer-events-none');
				});
				helpModal.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
					if (e.target === helpModal) {
						helpModal.classList.add('opacity-0', 'pointer-events-none');
					}
				});
			}

			// Help Modal Tabs Switch
			const helpTabButtons = document.querySelectorAll('.help-tab-btn');
			const helpTabPanes = document.querySelectorAll('.help-tab-pane');

			helpTabButtons.forEach(btn => {
				btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
					helpTabButtons.forEach(b => {
						b.classList.remove('text-emerald-400', 'border-emerald-500', 'bg-white/[0.02]');
						b.classList.add('text-gray-400', 'border-transparent');
					});
					helpTabPanes.forEach(p => p.classList.add('hidden'));

					btn.classList.add('text-emerald-400', 'border-emerald-500', 'bg-white/[0.02]');
					btn.classList.remove('text-gray-400', 'border-transparent');

					const targetPane = document.getElementById(btn.getAttribute('data-help-tab'));
					if (targetPane) targetPane.classList.remove('hidden');
				});
			});

			// Initial & Polling
			fetchEmails();
			fetchLogs();
			setInterval(() => {
				fetchEmails();
				fetchLogs();
			}, 3000);
		</script>
	</body>
</html>
